    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pullers to remove the bearing from the front of the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302445">Figure 45</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302445" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302445" filename="../figg13/G1302445.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 45. Use Pullers to Remove Bearing From Front of Output Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts and the rear bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302446">Figure 46</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302446" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302446" filename="../figg13/G1302446.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 46. Remove Bolts and Rear Bearing Cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the rear seal from the cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the speedometer gear or replacement spacer from the output shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the speedometer gear washer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From inside the housing, use a long punch to move the outer races of the countershaft rear
                bearings to the rear. Move races approximately 1/2 inch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302447">Figure 47</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302447" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302447" filename="../figg13/G1302447.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 47. Move Outer Races of Countershaft Rear Bearings to Rear</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the countershafts forward and out of the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302448">Figure 48</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302448" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302448" filename="../figg13/G1302448.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 48. Pull Countershafts Forward and Out of Housing</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
